`IFormFile` buffers the entire request body into memory by default. For large files, read the raw request body stream directly to disk:

```csharp
// Program.cs
app.MapPost("/upload", async (HttpRequest request) =>
{
    // Disable the default form body size limit
    if (!request.HasFormContentType)
        return Results.BadRequest("Expected multipart/form-data");

    var boundary = request.GetMultipartBoundary();
    if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(boundary))
        return Results.BadRequest("Missing boundary");

    var reader = new MultipartReader(boundary, request.Body);
    MultipartSection? section;

    while ((section = await reader.ReadNextSectionAsync()) != null)
    {
        if (ContentDispositionHeaderValue.TryParse(section.ContentDisposition, out var cd)
            && cd.IsFileDisposition())
        {
            var fileName = Path.GetRandomFileName(); // sanitize!
            var savePath = Path.Combine("/tmp/uploads", fileName);

            await using var stream = File.Create(savePath);
            await section.Body.CopyToAsync(stream);  // streams chunk-by-chunk
        }
    }

    return Results.Ok("Uploaded");
})
.DisableAntiforgery();
```

**Key configuration** (remove the default 28 MB cap):

```csharp
// Remove Kestrel's request body size limit
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(o =>
    o.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 2L * 1024 * 1024 * 1024); // 2 GB

// Remove the form options limit (even though we read manually, middleware may check)
builder.Services.Configure<FormOptions>(o =>
    o.MultipartBodyLengthLimit = 2L * 1024 * 1024 * 1024);
```

**Why this works:**
- `MultipartReader` reads the multipart stream section-by-section with a small internal buffer (default 80 KB).
- `CopyToAsync` flushes data to disk incrementally—memory stays flat regardless of file size.
- You never bind `IFormFile`, so ASP.NET Core never buffers the body.

**Additional tips:**
| Concern | Solution |
|---------|----------|
| Progress tracking | Count bytes in a custom `Stream` wrapper |
| Cancellation | Pass `CancellationToken` to `CopyToAsync` |
| Temp disk space | Use a dedicated volume for uploads |
| Reverse proxy limits | Set `client_max_body_size 2G;` in nginx or equivalent |
